# Lab 5 - Producer-Consumer pattern

This project shows an implementation of the producer-consumer pattern by using a custom Semaphore clas.  
**Author:** Adrien Dudon

## Requirements
- Compatible with **Linux** only
- A C++11 compiler (g++ will do fine)
- The Make program (should be already installed on your distro)

## Install
1. Clone this repository: `git clone git@github.com:Deewens/CDDLabs.git`
2. Go to Lab3/ directory: `cd Lab5`
3. Generate the doc (optional): `make doc`
4. Build project: `make`
5. Run: `./producerConsumer`

## Project/files Content
- **SafeBuffer:** thread safe buffer implementation, require Semaphore class
- **Sempahore:** implementation of a Semaphore
- **main.cpp:** the traditional start point of the program, showing off the Producer-Consumer implentation

